title: NIKU SOBA RECIPE è‚‰ãã°ãƒ¬ã‚·ãƒ” ðŸœ
content: #japanesefood #noodles #cooking #ramen #recipe #soba #japanesenoodles #japanesesoba #nikusoba #ãŠã™ã™ã‚ #ãŠã™ã™ã‚ã«ã®ã‚ŠãŸã„ #ç°¡å˜æ–™ç† #food #easyrecipe #beefnoodle #è‚‰ãã° #ãã°ãƒ¬ã‚·ãƒ” #è‚‰ãã°ãƒ¬ã‚·ãƒ” ðŸœ Niku Soba (Japanese Beef Soba Noodles) Tender beef simmered in a sweet-savory soy sauce broth, served over warm soba noodles with crunchy toppings. A cozy Japanese lunch favorite! ðŸ§‚ Ingredients (2 servings) For the beef marinade: 200 g thinly sliced beef 1 tbsp sake 1 tbsp mirin 1 tbsp soy sauce 1 tsp sugar 1 tsp ginger paste For the soba broth: 600 ml water 1 tbsp sake 2 tbsp mirin 3 tbsp soy sauce 1 tsp salt 1 tsp dashi powder 1 tsp sugar Other ingredients: 2 servings soba noodles (dried or fresh) Tempura bits (tenkasu), for topping 2 tbsp green onions, finely chopped A pinch of chili powder (shichimi or ichimi) ðŸ³ Instructions 1. Marinate the beef In a bowl, combine beef slices with sake, mirin, soy sauce, sugar, and ginger paste. Mix well and let marinate for at least 1 hour. 2. Prepare the broth In a pot, bring water, sake, mirin, soy sauce, salt, dashi powder, and sugar to a gentle boil. Once combined, remove from heat and set aside. 3. Cook the beef In a frying pan, cook the marinated beef over medium heat until tender and cooked through. Set aside. 4. Cook the soba Boil soba noodles according to package instructions. Drain well and divide into bowls. 5. Assemble Pour hot broth over the soba noodles. Top with cooked beef, tempura bits, green onions, and a sprinkle of chili powder. 6. Serve Enjoy warm and comforting niku soba with your favorite side dishes! ðŸœ è‚‰ãã°ï¼ˆç‰›è‚‰ãã°ï¼‰ ç”˜è¾›ã„é†¤æ²¹ã ã‚Œã§ç…®ãŸã‚„ã‚ã‚‰ã‹ã„ç‰›è‚‰ã‚’ã€æ¸©ã‹ã„ãã°ã«ã®ã›ã¦ã„ãŸã ãä¸€å“ã€‚ã‚µã‚¯ã‚µã‚¯ã®å¤©ã‹ã™ã‚„è–¬å‘³ã‚’æ·»ãˆã¦ã€ã»ã£ã¨ã™ã‚‹æ—¥æœ¬ã®ãƒ©ãƒ³ãƒã«ã´ã£ãŸã‚Šã§ã™ï¼ ðŸ§‚ ææ–™ï¼ˆ2äººåˆ†ï¼‰ ç‰›è‚‰ã®ä¸‹å‘³ç”¨ ç‰›è‚‰ï¼ˆè–„åˆ‡ã‚Šï¼‰ â€¦ 200g é…’ â€¦ å¤§ã•ã˜1 ã¿ã‚Šã‚“ â€¦ å¤§ã•ã˜1 é†¤æ²¹ â€¦ å¤§ã•ã˜1 ç ‚ç³– â€¦ å°ã•ã˜1 ãŠã‚ã—ç”Ÿå§œ â€¦ å°ã•ã˜1 ãã°ã¤ã‚† æ°´ â€¦ 600ml é…’ â€¦ å¤§ã•ã˜1 ã¿ã‚Šã‚“ â€¦ å¤§ã•ã˜2 é†¤æ²¹ â€¦ å¤§ã•ã˜3 å¡© â€¦ å°ã•ã˜1 ã ã—ã®ç´  â€¦ å°ã•ã˜1 ç ‚ç³– â€¦ å°ã•ã˜1 ãã®ä»– ãã°ï¼ˆç”Ÿã¾ãŸã¯ä¹¾éººï¼‰ â€¦ 2äººåˆ† å¤©ã‹ã™ â€¦ é©é‡ é’ã­ãŽï¼ˆå°å£åˆ‡ã‚Šï¼‰ â€¦ å¤§ã•ã˜2 ä¸ƒå‘³ã¾ãŸã¯ä¸€å‘³å”è¾›å­ â€¦ å°‘ã€… ðŸ³ ä½œã‚Šæ–¹ 1. ç‰›è‚‰ã‚’ä¸‹å‘³ã«æ¼¬ã‘ã‚‹ ãƒœã‚¦ãƒ«ã«ç‰›è‚‰ã‚’å…¥ã‚Œã€é…’ãƒ»ã¿ã‚Šã‚“ãƒ»é†¤æ²¹ãƒ»ç ‚ç³–ãƒ»ãŠã‚ã—ç”Ÿå§œã‚’åŠ ãˆã¦ã‚ˆãæ··ãœã€å°‘ãªãã¨ã‚‚1æ™‚é–“æ¼¬ã‘è¾¼ã‚€ã€‚ 2. ãã°ã¤ã‚†ã‚’ä½œã‚‹ é‹ã«æ°´ãƒ»é…’ãƒ»ã¿ã‚Šã‚“ãƒ»é†¤æ²¹ãƒ»å¡©ãƒ»ã ã—ã®ç´ ãƒ»ç ‚ç³–ã‚’å…¥ã‚Œã€ä¸­ç«ã«ã‹ã‘ã¦è»½ãæ²¸é¨°ã•ã›ã‚‹ã€‚å‘³ãŒãªã˜ã‚“ã ã‚‰ç«ã‚’æ­¢ã‚ã¦ãŠãã€‚ 3. ç‰›è‚‰ã‚’èª¿ç†ã™ã‚‹ ãƒ•ãƒ©ã‚¤ãƒ‘ãƒ³ã§ä¸‹å‘³ã‚’ã¤ã‘ãŸç‰›è‚‰ã‚’ä¸­ç«ã§ç‚’ã‚ã€ç«ãŒé€šã‚‹ã¾ã§åŠ ç†±ã™ã‚‹ã€‚å–ã‚Šå‡ºã—ã¦ãŠãã€‚ 4. ãã°ã‚’èŒ¹ã§ã‚‹ ãã°ã‚’è¢‹ã®è¡¨ç¤ºé€šã‚Šã«èŒ¹ã§ã‚‹ã€‚èŒ¹ã§ä¸ŠãŒã£ãŸã‚‰æ¹¯ã‚’åˆ‡ã‚Šã€å™¨ã«ç››ã‚‹ã€‚ 5. ç››ã‚Šä»˜ã‘ã‚‹ å™¨ã®ãã°ã«ç†±ã„ã¤ã‚†ã‚’æ³¨ãŽã€ç‰›è‚‰ã‚’ã®ã›ã‚‹ã€‚ã•ã‚‰ã«å¤©ã‹ã™ãƒ»é’ã­ãŽãƒ»å”è¾›å­ã‚’ãƒˆãƒƒãƒ”ãƒ³ã‚°ã™ã‚‹ã€‚ 6. å®Œæˆï¼ ç†±ã€…ã®è‚‰ãã°ã‚’å¬ã—ä¸ŠãŒã‚Œï¼ãŠå¥½ã¿ã§å°é‰¢ãªã©ã‚’æ·»ãˆã¦ã‚‚â—Ž

title: STADION AJINOMOTO MIRIP DENGAN GBKâ€¼ï¸ MARKAS KLUB FC TOKYO DAN TOKYO VERDY
content: Ajinomoto Stadium (juga dikenal sebagai Tokyo Stadium) adalah stadion multi-fungsi yang terletak di ChÅfu, Tokyo, Jepang. Dibuka pada tahun 2001, stadion ini berkapasitas sekitar 50.000 penonton dan menjadi markas bagi dua klub J-League: FC Tokyo dan Tokyo Verdy. Stadion ini tidak hanya digunakan untuk pertandingan sepak bola, tetapi juga untuk rugby, konser musik, festival, hingga menjadi tempat evakuasi saat bencana (seperti gempa dan tsunami 2011). Ajinomoto Stadium menjadi salah satu venue penting saat Piala Dunia Rugby 2019 dan Olimpiade Tokyo 2020. Secara arsitektural, stadion ini memiliki atap berbentuk lingkaran yang menutupi sebagian besar tribun, dilengkapi panel surya dan fitur ramah lingkungan seperti green wall dan turbin angin kecil. Sistem pencahayaan LED canggih-nya mendukung siaran kualitas 4K/8K. Akses menuju stadion sangat mudah, hanya beberapa menit berjalan kaki dari Stasiun TobitakyÅ« di Jalur Keio. #stadion #ajinomoto #jis #jepang #gbk #football #footballclub

Enjoy! *You can serve with Okonomiyaki sauce, mayonnaise, bonito flakes, and dried seaweed flakes. #TastyJapan #ãƒ¬ã‚·ãƒ” MUSIC Licensed via Epidemic Sound
